26/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Monday (26 January), Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan will leave for a six-day visit to the United States, accompanied by Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul, Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul and Economy Minister Ali Babacan.
The trip begins with talks with representatives of the World Bank and IMF.
On Wednesday, Erdogan is scheduled to meet with President George W. Bush about Cyprus, the situation in Iraq, and Turkey's aspirations for EU membership.
Erdogan last met with Bush in Washington in December 2002, just before he became prime minister.
(AFP - 25/01/04)
